The paper focuses on analyzing bias in deep learning-based face recognition systems, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the sub-conscious behavior of face recognition models, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper takes cues from cognitive studies, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
